# Operational Risk Control Framework

## Overview

Operational risk controls help organizations prevent errors, disruptions, and financial losses within wholesale operations.

Risk controls are checkpoints within operational workflows that verify accuracy before processes move forward.

---

## Purpose

Risk controls are designed to:

• prevent operational errors  
• reduce financial risk  
• maintain compliance with retailer requirements  
• protect shipment timelines  
• ensure data accuracy across systems  

These controls help stabilize operations as order volumes increase.

---

## Key Risk Areas

Wholesale operations face risks in several areas, including:

### Order Accuracy

Risks may include:

• incorrect SKU selection  
• pricing errors  
• invalid order quantities  

Validation checkpoints reduce these risks.

### System Integration

Risks may include:

• EDI transmission failures  
• incorrect data mapping  
• delayed system updates  

Monitoring integration performance helps detect issues early.

### Logistics Compliance

Risks may include:

• routing guide violations  
• incorrect carrier selection  
• shipment delays  

Compliance reviews help prevent penalties.

### Financial Accuracy

Risks may include:

• incorrect invoice values  
• duplicate invoices  
• unresolved deductions  

Financial review processes reduce billing errors.

---

## Risk Control Points

Operational controls may include:

• order validation checkpoints  
• system monitoring alerts  
• shipment compliance reviews  
• invoice validation procedures  
• exception management tracking  

These controls help detect issues before they escalate.

---

## Monitoring and Review

Risk controls should be reviewed regularly through:

• operational KPI monitoring  
• issue log analysis  
• audit reviews  
• process performance evaluations  

Reviewing risk controls helps organizations maintain operational discipline.

---

## Final Note

Operational risk controls are essential for maintaining stable wholesale operations. Strong control processes help organizations prevent errors, reduce financial risk, and maintain service reliability.
